<SECOND>AM-Murder-Suicide,0418</SECOND>
<HEAD>Child Actress And Parents Dead In Apparent Murder-Suicide</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto LA10, 11</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MICHAEL FLEEMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A child actress who starred in last summer's `` Jaws IV: The Revenge'' was killed with her mother Wednesday in an apparent murder-suicide initiated by her father, who also died, authorities said The coroner had not yet identified the couple and the child, but neighbors said the girl was <PERSON> Judith </PERSON> <PERSON> Barsi </PERSON>, 11, who starred in the third sequel to the series about a man-eating shark. Miss <PERSON> Barsi </PERSON> also appeared in the partly fact-based television movie `` Fatal Vision,'' playing a daughter of Dr. <PERSON> Jeffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> MacDonald </PERSON>, who was convicted of killing his pregnant wife and both his daughters at <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bragg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION>, in 1970. Miss <PERSON> Barsi </PERSON>'s father apparently shot the girl and the mother in their heads, set the inside of the house on fire, then turned the gun on himself, police said. The fire caused extensive damage to the interior of the home. A researcher at <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Studios </ORGANIZATION> confirmed Miss <PERSON> Barsi </PERSON> starred in `` Jaws IV: The Revenge'' as a character called `` Thea.'' She also performed in several commercials and had appeared in the television show `` Growing Pains,'' neighbors said. `` She was adorable ... quite precocious, blonde and blue-eyed,'' said former neighbor <PERSON> Adrienne </PERSON> <PERSON> Conway </PERSON>. She said the mother and father had been having marital problems. Neighbors said they heard an explosion at 8:30 a.m., then saw flames shooting out of a front window of the tan, single-story house on a quiet street. One neighbor tried to douse the flames with water from a garden hose until firefighters arrived. Officers at the scene said the father, identified by neighbors as <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Barsi </PERSON>, apparently doused the interior of the couple's home with gasoline and set it ablaze before sho