<HEAD>Rumbling Beneath Volcano Draws Attention</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAUL JENKINS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Scores of small quakes have rattled an Aleut fishing village during the past 17 days, and geologists say they are keeping a wary eye on the possible source: a volcano that's been dormant for centuries. King Cove village is only nine miles from <ORGANIZATION> Mount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dutton </ORGANIZATION>'s 4,834-foot peak About 1,000 people live in the village during the summer; 700 stay through winter. Aside from the earthquakes that have been jolting the community 625 miles southwest of <LOCATION> Anchorage </LOCATION>, there have been no other signs of an imminent eruption, said <PERSON> Betsy </PERSON> <PERSON> Yount </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Geological Survey geologist here. `` There's no melting back of snow around the summit. No steam-type vents,'' sher said Wednesday. `` We're still assessing the seismic activity to determine whether it's related to volcanic activity or not.'' Geologists are unsure when <PERSON> Mount </PERSON> <PERSON> Dutton </PERSON> last erupted. `` There's no historical records of its erupting. That means in the past 200 or so years,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Davies </PERSON>, state seismologist and coordinating scientist for the newly formed <ORGANIZATION> Alaska </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Volcano </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Observatory </ORGANIZATION>. `` It may have erupted 500 years ago, but we have no date. Clearly, it's erupted in the last 10,000 years or so.'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Taber </PERSON>, a geologist with <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Lamont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Doherty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Geological </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Observatory </ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION> Palisades </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, said seismographs first picked up earthquake activity near <LOCATION> Mount </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dutton </LOCATION> on July 11. Some of the 18 instru