/ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alaska-Fairbanks </ORGANIZATION> can monitor <PERSON> Taber </PERSON>'s seismographs, plus one <PERSON> Davies </PERSON> recently installed on the mountain's <PERSON> Taber </PERSON> has been in <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> servicing his observatory's seismographs and plans to leave this week, <PERSON> Davies </PERSON> said The link will allow scientists in Fairbanks to check the volcano's pulse virtually around the clock, he said. `` We're going to monitor it as closely as we can,'' he said.
