<BYLINE>By PETER ENG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOGOR, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>'s prime minister was quoted Thursday as saying <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> guerrilla delegates tried to obstruct agreements at talks on ending <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION>'s civil war. The <ORGANIZATION> Jakarta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> quoted Prime Minister <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON> of the Vietnamese-installed government as saying he would hold a third round of separate peace talks with resistance leader Prince <PERSON> Norodom </PERSON> <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> in October. <PERSON> Sihanouk </PERSON>'s forces are allied with the communist <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Son </PERSON> <PERSON> Sann </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> in a coalition fighting Vietnamese troops that invaded <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION> in late 1978. <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON>, the guerrilla groups, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Laos </LOCATION> and the six-member <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southeast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Asian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday began their fourth day of informal peace talks in <LOCATION> Bogor </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Jakarta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> reported that <PERSON> Hun </PERSON> <PERSON> Sen </PERSON> said <PERSON> Khieu </PERSON> <PERSON> Samphan </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> representative, `` was not forthcoming to the point of acting obstructive when it came to nailing down some specific points o