<HEAD>Reagan Sees Resurgence In Religion, Family Values</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MERRILL HARTSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said today the nation is regaining its `` religious and moral bearings'' but must do more to overcome promiscuity, drug use, pornography and a drifting away from church and family values. `` An overwhelming nine out of 10 Americans pray,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said. `` Audiences for religious books are growing. The modern communications media are being used for evangelism.'' In a speech to the <ORGANIZATION> Student </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> on Evangelism at the <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Convention </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, the president said his administration `` has worked hard to reflect this return to basic values.'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> ticked off a host of steps in recent years, including enactment by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> of the Equal Access Act of 1984, giving voluntary religious groups the right to meet after school on the same basis as other groups. He also cited longstanding administration positions in support of returning prayer to the classroom and reversing the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> decision that legalized abortions. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> seldom goes to church, but has said he prays frequently. In his speech today, he said that `` I am not going to preach a sermon.'' At another point, the president talked to the young men and women about the pressures teen-agers feel to have sex out of wedlock. `` I'm sure that each of you believes that someday you'll find someone to fall in love with _ and you will,'' he said. `` Sometimes you may get frustrated and, yes, finding the right one may take longer than you thought. `` But do n't worry. It will happen,'' <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> said. `` And that's why it's so important for you not to pay any attention at all to those who say that promiscuity is somehow stylish and rewarding No, the right thing to