 its economic program of substantial price increases and hefty wage cuts. The measures, made in conjunction with the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monetary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fund </ORGANIZATION>, are designed to curb inflation and help repay the foreign debt by introducing a more market-oriented economy. `` The May measures are a strong and brave economic program, and they were accepted as such by our foreign creditors,'' <PERSON> Zemljaric </PERSON> said.
