<TEXT>
 A <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> drug agent who was kidnapped and killed while investigating a narcotics empire in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> was beaten so severely that his skull looked like a cracked eggshell, a prosecutor said Thursday. In his opening statement to jurors, Assistant <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Gurule </PERSON> said <PERSON> Enrique </PERSON> <PERSON> Camarena </PERSON>, a Drug Enforcement Administration agent, died what he called a barbaric death in a torture chamber. The prosecutor outlined the evidence he plans to present to the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> jury hearing the trial of three Mexican nationals charged in the case. The trial is expected to take about 10 weeks.
