<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce 142,941 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's 156,536, <PERSON> Ward </PERSON>'s Automotive Reports said Thursday This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago, when 142,090 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal said. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> automakers were scheduled to make 76,751 cars this week, compared with 88,055 a week ago and 72,305 in the same week in 1987. Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 66,190, compared with last week's 68,481 and last year's 69,785. Canadian automakers were to build 9,155 cars this week, up from 5,444 a week ago and from last year's 7,727. Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 11,934, compared with 5,488 a week ago and 6,652 in the same week last year.
